                {
                    "id": "equal_OH_HO2_initial",
                    "description": "Initial-condition sensitivity check: start the system at OH = HO2 = 5.5e12 m^-3 (so HOx = 1.1e13 same as the default case). The system should still relax to the same steady state as the default (OH ≈ 1.689e12, HO2 ≈ 9.311e12) because the steady-state ratio depends only on the rate coefficients and the per-cell environment T, O, O3, NO — not on the initial partition between OH and HO2. Verifies the initial-condition machinery works correctly and that the steady-state attractor is uniquely determined by the parameter set.",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 3600.0},
