                            "x": {"variable": "T", "label": "Temperature (K)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "HO2", "label": "HO2 (m^-3)"}
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "NO_recycle_sensitivity_sweep",
                    "description": "NO-recycle sweep across the stratospheric NOx range (1e10 - 1e16 m^-3). The HO2+NO channel is the dominant HOx recycle pathway under typical mid-stratosphere conditions (S&P Eq. 5.28). Sweeping NO illustrates the transition between two regimes: at low NO, HO2+O3 and HO2+O carry the recycle alone and the steady-state OH/HO2 ratio is small; at high NO, HO2+NO dominates and the OH/HO2 ratio approaches a NO-independent limit.",
